Resolve ${localWorkspaceFolder} in client-side substitution pass

The client resolved ${localEnv:...} before sending the devcontainer
config to the daemon, but left workspace folder variables for the
daemon's second pass. This caused resolved_mounts() to reject
${localWorkspaceFolder} in bind mount sources when called from
validate_bind_mount_ownership() on the client side.

Also remove #[derive(Default)] from SubstitutionContext so that
adding a new variable causes compile errors at every construction
site, preventing silent omissions like this one.
